    "intro": "Interpretation asks what the text means — moving from observation (what does it say?) to discerning the psalmist's intent in his original canonical context and its trajectory into the New Testament. The movements below trace the psalm's argument across its three structural units: the indicative foundation (vv.1-3), the human imperative (vv.4-6), and the cosmic imperative and eschatological warrant (vv.7-9). Where the original Hebrew sharpens what the English translation carries, a brief note follows.",
